DUBAI DUTY FREE TENNIS CHAMPIONSHIPS
February 27, 2017
Roberto Bautista Agut
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT








R. BAUTISTA AGUT/K. Khachanov
6-1, 7-6
THE MODERATOR: Questions, please.
Q. Will you play Belgrade Davis Cup?
ROBERTO BAUTISTA AGUT: Well, for the moment, yes, no?  Still five weeks to go to Belgrade, but we will see, no?  Still three good tournaments to play before Davis Cup, but for the moment, if the captain wants me to play there, for sure.
Q. What do you expect there?  Do you expect to win or big battle?
ROBERTO BAUTISTA AGUT: In Belgrade?
Q. Yeah.
ROBERTO BAUTISTA AGUT: Well, for sure it's gonna be good and great atmosphere right there.  And Serbia has a great team.  They are good players.  They have also good doubles.
And we play outside, we play indoor hard, for sure.  We will have to play unbelievable to beat them.
Q. Have you heard anything about the place where they are going to play?  It's famous because of atmosphere in basketball.  Have you heard about it?
ROBERTO BAUTISTA AGUT: No, I didn't hear.
Q. Will Nadal play?
ROBERTO BAUTISTA AGUT: We hope yes (smiling).
Q. Do you expect Djokovic to play?
ROBERTO BAUTISTA AGUT: Of course.  Why not?






END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT